enewconfederatearmy.tripod.com/home.html|title=Home|website=thenewconfederatearmy.tripod.com|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref>\n\n==French Overseas Departments and Collectivities==\n{{Main|Secession in France}}\n\n{{flagicon|France}} [[Martinique]]\n* Proposed state: [[Image:Flag of the Front National de Lib\u00e9ration de la Martinique.svg|22px|border]] Republic of Martinique\n** Political party: [[Martinican Progressive Party]], [[Image:Bandera del MIM.svg|22px|border]] [[Martinican Independence Movement]]\n\n{{flagicon|France}} [[Guadeloupe]] \n* Proposed state: [[Image:FLNG.svg|22px|border]] Republic of Guadeloupe\n** Political party: [[United Guadeloupe, Solidary and Responsible]], [[Progressive Democratic Party of Guadeloupe]], [[Plural Left (Guadeloupe)|Plural Left]] and the [[Guadeloupean Objective]]\n\n{{flagicon|France}} [[Collectivity of Saint Martin|Saint Martin]]\n* Proposed state: [[File:Flag of Saint-Martin (fictional).svg|22px|border]] Republic of Saint Martin\n** Political party: [[Rally Responsibility Success]], [[Succeed Saint Martin]], [[Union for Progress (Saint Martin)|Union for Progress]], [[Union for Progress (Saint Martin)|Union for Progress]] and the [[Democratic Alliance for Saint Martin]]\n\n{{Flagicon|France}} [[Saint Barthelemy]]\n* Proposed state: Republic of Saint Barthelemy\n** Political party: [[Saint Barth First!]]\n\n{{Flagicon|France}} [[Saint Pierre and Miquelon]]\n* Proposed State: Republic of Saint Pierre and Miquelon\n** Political party: [[Together for the Future]], [[Saint Pierre and Miquelon 2000]]\n\n==See also==\n* [[Lists of active separatist movements]]\n* [[List of historical separatist movements]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n{{Separatist movements per continent}}\n{{Secession in Countries}}\n{{Irredentism}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Active Separatist Movements In North America, List Of}}\n[[Category:North America-related lists|Separatist Movements, Active]]\n[[Category:Disputed territories in North America|Separatist Movements In North America, Active]]\n[[Category:Lists of active separatist movements|North America]]\n[[Category:Society-related lists|Separatist Movements In North America, Active]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Refimprove|date=March 2008}}\nThis is a '''list of currently active [[Separatism|separatist]] movements in [[North America]]'''. Separatism includes [[autonomism]] and [[secession]]ism. What is and is not considered an autonomist or secessionist movement is sometimes contentious. Entries on this list must meet three criteria:\n# They are active movements with living, active members.\n# They are seeking greater autonomy or self-determination for a geographic region.\n# They are the citizen/peoples of the conflict area and do not come from other countries.\n\nUnder each region listed is one or more of the following:\n* ''De facto'' state: for regions with ''[[de facto]]'' autonomy from the government\n* Proposed state: proposed name for a seceding [[sovereign state]]\n* Proposed autonomous area: for movements toward greater [[Autonomous area|autonomy for an area]] but not outright secession\n** ''De facto'' autonomous government: for governments with ''de facto'' autonomous control over a region\n** Government-in-exile: for a [[Government in exile|government based outside of the region in question]], with or without control\n** Political party (or parties): for [[Political party|political parties]] involved in a political system to push for autonomy or secession\n** Militant organisation(s): for armed organisations (sometimes called [[Terrorism|terrorist organisations]])\n** Advocacy group(s): for [[Advocacy group|non-belligerent, non-politically participatory entities]]\n** [[Ethnic]]/[[ethno-religious]]/[[racial]]/[[Regionalism (politics)|regional]]/[[Religious organization|religious]] group(s)\n\n==Canada==\n{{Main article|Secessionist movements of Canada}}\n\n;Secessionist movements\n[[File:Women's March on Portland - 71.jpg|thumb|190px|The [[Doug flag]] at the [[Women's March on Portland]]]]\n[[File:Quebec_referendum,_1995_-_Results_By_Riding.svg|thumb|225px|Results of the [[1995 Quebec independence referendum]]. 49.42% voted in favour of independence.]]\n\n[[File:Flag of Alberta.svg|22px|border]] [[Alberta]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/nov/25/wexit-alberta-canada-independence-separatism|title=Wexit: Alberta's frustration fuels push for independence from Canada|last=Cecco|first=Leyland|date=25 November 2019|work=The Guardian|access-date=25 November 2019|last2=Agren|first2=David|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>\n{{main|Alberta separatism}}\n* Proposed state: [[File:Flag of Alberta.svg|22px|border]] [[Alberta]] or part as Western Canada\n** Political party: Wexit Party\n\n[[File:Flag of British Columbia.svg|22px|border]] [[British Columbia]] together with the [[File:Flag of Cascadia.svg|22px|border]] [[Pacific Northwest|Pacific Northwestern US]] ([[List of active separatist movements in North America#United States|United States]])\n{{Main|Cascadia (independence movement)}}\n* Proposed state: [[File:Flag of Cascadia.svg|22px|border]] [[Cascadia (independence movement)|Cascadia]]\n** Political party: [[BC Cascadia Party]], Cascadian Independence Party\n\n[[File:Flag of New Brunswick.svg|22px|border]]/[[File:Flag of Prince Edward Island.svg|22px|border]]/[[File:Flag of Nova Scotia.svg|22px|border]] [[The Maritimes]]: [[New Brunswick]], [[Prince Edward Island]], & [[Nova Scotia]]\n* Ethnic group: [[Acadians]]\n** Proposed state: [[File:Flag of Acadia.svg|22px|border]] [[Acadia]]\n\n[[File:Flag_of_Newfoundland_and_Labrador.svg|22px|border]] [[Newfoundland and Labrador]]\n{{Main|Secessionist movements of Canada#Newfoundland & Labrador}}\n* Proposed State: [[File:Newfoundland Tricolour.svg|22px|border]] [[Newfoundland and Labrador]] \n\n[[File:Flag of Quebec.svg|22px|border]] [[Quebec]]\n{{main|Quebec sovereignty movement}}\n* Regional group: [[Qu\u00e9b\u00e9cois people]]\n** Proposed state: [[File:Flag of Quebec.svg|22px|border]] [[Quebec|Republic of Quebec]]\n*** Civil organization: [[Saint-Jean-Baptiste Society]], [[Mouvement national des Qu\u00e9b\u00e9coises et des Qu\u00e9b\u00e9cois|Mouvement national des Qu\u00e9b\u00e9cois et des Qu\u00e9b\u00e9coises]] (MNQ), [[Rassemblement pour l'ind\u00e9pendance du Qu\u00e9bec]] (RIQ), [[Les Intellectuels pour la souverainet\u00e9]] (IPSO), [[Mouvement de Lib\u00e9ration Nationale du Qu\u00e9bec|Mouvement de lib\u00e9ration nationale du Qu\u00e9bec]] (MLNQ), [[R\u00e9seau de R\u00e9sistance du Qu\u00e9becois]] (RRQ)\n*** Labour union: [[Conf\u00e9d\u00e9ration des syndicats nationaux]] (CSN), [[Centrale des syndicats du Qu\u00e9bec]] (CSQ), [[F\u00e9d\u00e9ration des travailleurs du Qu\u00e9bec]] (FTQ), [[Union des artistes]] (UDA)\n*** Political party: [[Parti Qu\u00e9b\u00e9cois]], [[Bloc Qu\u00e9b\u00e9cois]], [[Qu\u00e9bec solidaire]], [[Marxist\u2013Leninist Party of Quebec]]\n\n[[File:Flag of Saskatchewan.svg|22px|border]] [[Saskatchewan]]\n* Proposed state: [[File:Flag of Saskatchewan.svg|22px|border]] [[Saskatchewan|Republic of Saskatchewan]] or part as [[Western Canada Independence Party|Western Canada]]\n** Political party: [[Western Independence Party of Saskatchewan]]\n\n[[Vancouver Island]]\n* Proposed state: [[File:Flag of Vancouver Island.svg|22px|border]] [[Vancouver Island]]\n** Political party: [[Vancouver Island Party]]\n\n[[Haida Gwaii]]\n\n* Proposed state: [[File:Flag of Haida.svg|alt=|border|22x22px]] [[Council of the Haida Nation|Haida Nation]]\n\n[[File:Flag of Alberta.svg|22px|border]]/[[File:Flag of British Columbia.svg|22px|border]]/[[File:Flag of Manitoba.svg|22px|border]]/[[File:Flag of Saskatchewan.svg|22px|border]] [[Secessionist movements of Canada#Western Canada|Western Canada]]\n{{main|Western alienation}}\n* Proposed state: Western Canada\n** Political party: [[Wexit Canada]], [[Western Canada Independence Party]]\n*** Pressure group: [[Alberta_separatism#Wexit|Wexit]] \n\n;Autonomist movements\n[[File:Flag of Alberta.svg|22px|border]] [[Alberta]] \n* Proposed autonomous area: [[File:Flag of Alberta.svg|22px|border]] [[Alberta]] \n** Political party: [[Freedom Conservative Party of Alberta]]<ref>https://www.freedomconservativeparty.ca/principles</ref>, [[Alberta Independence Party]]\n\n[[File:Flag of Quebec.svg|22px|border]] [[Quebec]]\n* Proposed autonomous area: [[File:Flag of Quebec.svg|22px|border]] [[Quebec]]\n** Political party: [[Coalition Avenir Qu\u00e9bec]], [[\u00c9quipe Autonomiste]]\n\n==Denmark==\n{{Main|Secession in Denmark}}\n\n;Secessionist movements\n:''For other movements in [[Denmark]], see [[List of active separatist movements in Europe#Denmark|List of active separatist movements in Europe]].''\n\nGreenland is geographically part of North America, but is politically connected to Europe.\n\n[[File:Flag of Greenland.svg|22px|border]] [[Greenland]]\n{{main|Greenlandic independence}}\n* Ethnic group: [[Greenlandic Inuit]]\n** Proposed state: {{flag|Greenland|name=Greenland}}\n*** Political party: [[Inuit Ataqatigiit]], [[Forward (Greenland)|Forward]], and [[Partii Naleraq]]\n\n== Mexico ==\n{{Main|Secession in Mexico}}\n\n=== Ethnolingustic regions ===\n\n[[File: Flag_of_the_Aridoamerican_States_Confederation.png|22px|border]][[Aridoamerica]]\n* Ethnic group: [[Aridoamericans]], [[Chicanos]]\n** Proposed States: [[File: Flag_of_the_Aridoamerican_States_Confederation.png|22px|border]] [[Aridoamerican States Confederation]], [[File: Flag_of_the_Republic_of_the_Rio_Grande.svg|22px|border]] [[Republic of the Rio Grande]], [[File:Flag of the Republic of Sonora.svg|22px|border]] [[Republic of Sonora]], [[File: Flag_of_Texas.svg|22px|border]] [[Republic of Texas]], [[File:Flag of the Republic of Lower California.svg|22px|border]] [[Republic of Baja California]]\n*** Advocacies: \n**** Aridoamerican Identitarian Movement\n**** Aridoamerica Project\n**** (* 1953, \u2020 2015)[[Charles A. Truxillo]]\n*** Political parties: None\n*** Related: [[Jaime Rodr\u00edguez Calder\u00f3n|El Bronco]], [[Claudia Pavlovich Arellano|Claudia Pavlovich]], [[Javier Corral Jurado|Javier Corral]], [[Miguel \u00c1ngel Riquelme Sol\u00eds|Miguel Riquelme]], [[Francisco Javier Garc\u00eda Cabeza de Vaca| FJGCDV]]\n\n=== Mexican regions ===\n\n[[Baja California Peninsula|Baja California]] <ref> https://www.sandiegored.com/en/news/73065/Separatist-Group-seeks-independence-for-Baja-California-Mexico </ref>\n* Ethnic group: [[Bajacalifornians]]\n** Proposed state: [[File:Flag of the Republic of Lower California.svg|22px|border]] [[Republic of Baja California]]\n*** Advocacies: [[Baja California Independence Movement]]\n*** Political parties: [[Baja California Republican Movement]]\n*** Movement: [[Baja California Independence Movement]]\n*** Militant organization: [[Separatist Army of the Sovereign State of Baja California]]\n\n=== Mexican states===\n\n[[File:Flag of Sonora.svg|22px|border]] [[Sonora]]\n* Ethnic group: [[Mexicans|Sonorense]]\n** Proposed state: [[File:Flag of the Republic of Sonora.svg|22px|border]] [[Republic of Sonora]]\n*** Advocacy movements: [[Free Sonora]], [[New Republic of Sonora]]\n*** Political party: [[Separatist Movement of the Northern States]]\n\n[[File:Flag of Yucatan.svg|22px|border]] [[Yucat\u00e1n]]\n* Ethnic group: [[Mexicans]], [[Maya peoples|Mayans]]\n** Proposed state: [[File:Flag of the Republic of Yucatan.svg|22px|border]] [[Republic of Yucat\u00e1n]]\n*** Political party: [[Alliance for Yucatan Party]]\n\n[[File:Flag of the EZLN.svg|22px|border]] [[Zapatista Army of National Liberation|Zapatista (Chiapas)]]\n* Ethnic group: [[Chiapas|Chiapas Mayas]]\n** De facto autonomous area: [[File:Flag of the EZLN.svg|22px|border]] [[Rebel Zapatista Autonomous Municipalities]]\n*** Political parties: [[Council of Good Government]] \n*** Militant organization: [[Zapatista Army of National Liberation]]\n\n==Nicaragua==\n{{Main|Secession in Nicaragua}}\n\n[[File:Flag of Miskito - Minahan.svg|22px|border]] [[Mosquito Coast|Mosquito]]\n* Ethnic group: [[Miskito people]]\n** Proposed state: [[Mosquito Coast#Miskito separatism|Communitarian Nation of Moskitia]]\n\n==Saint Kitts and Nevis==\n{{Main|Secession in Saint Kitts and Nevis}}\n\n{{flag|Nevis}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.caribbeannetnews.com/cgi-script/csArticles/articles/000020/002025.htm|title=Independence for Nevis still on the agenda, says premier|last=|first=|date=2006-07-16|website=Caribbean Net News|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060808185131/http://www.caribbeannetnews.com/cgi-script/csArticles/articles/000020/002025.htm|archive-date=2006-08-08|access-date=2019-03-19}}</ref> \n* Proposed state: Dominion of [[Nevis]].\n* Political parties: [[Nevis Reformation Party]], [[Concerned Citizens' Movement]]\n\n==United States==\n{{Main|Secession in the United States}}\n\n;Secessionist movements\n[[File:Flag_of_Alaska.svg|22px|border]] [[Alaska|Republic of Alaska]]\n* Proposed state: [[Alaska]]\n** Ethnic group: [[Alaska Natives]]\n* Political party: [[Alaskan Independence Party]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.akip.org/|title=Alaskan Independence Party}}</ref>\n\n[[File:RNA Flag 08I09.svg|22px|border]] [[Republic of New Afrika|New Afrika]]\n* Proposed state: Republic of New Afrika\n** Ethnic group: [[African Americans|Afro-Americans]]\n**Proposed entity: Includes Louisiana, Alabama, South Carolina, Georgia, and Mississippi \n\n[[File:Flag of California.svg|22px|border]] [[California]]\n* Proposed state: Second Californian Republic/\"New\" California\n** Pressure groups: [[Yes California]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yescalifornia.org/}}</ref> Californians for Independence<ref>{{cite web|url=http://CaforIndependence.co}}</ref>\n** Political party: [[California National Party]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://californianational.party}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Flag of Cascadia.svg|22px|border]] [[Cascadia (independence movement)|Cascadia]] (including [[File:Flag_of_Washington.svg|22px|border]] [[Washington (state)|Washington]], [[File:Flag_of_Oregon.svg|22px|border]] [[Oregon]], and the Canadian province of [[File:Flag_of_British Columbia.svg|22px|border]]  [[British Columbia]])\n{{Main|Cascadia (independence movement)}}\n* Proposed state: [[File:Flag of Cascadia.svg|22px|border]] [[Cascadia (independence movement)|Cascadia]]\n** Pressure group: [[Cascadia (independence movement)|Cascadia Independence Movement]]\n\n[[File:Flag of Hawaii.svg|22px|border]] [[Hawaii]]<ref>Hawaii is not geographically in the continent of North America, but is politically part of it.</ref>\n{{Main article|Hawaiian sovereignty movement}}\n* Ethnic group: [[Native Hawaiians]]\n** Pressure groups: [[Nation of Hawai\u02bbi (organization)|Nation of Hawai\u02bbi]], [[Office of Hawaiian Affairs]]\n** Political party: Hawaii Independence Party\n\n[[File:Northwest Territorial Imperative flag.svg|22px|border]] [[Northwest Territorial Imperative]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.adl.org/education/references/hate-symbols/northwest-american-republic|title=North American Republic|website=Anti-Defamation League|language=en|access-date=2019-12-13}}</ref><ref>[https://fotw.info/flags/us%7Dnaz.html#nwf Nazi and Neo-Nazi Flags in the United States, Northwest Front, Flags of the World]</ref>\n* Ethnic group: [[White Americans]]\n** Proposed state: Northwest American Republic\n** Pressure groups: [[White Aryan Resistance]], [[Aryan Nations]], Northwestern Imperative, <ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=Sf_WAAAAMAAJ|title=Gods of the Blood: The Pagan Revival and White Separatism|last=Gardell|first=Mattias|date=2003-06-27|publisher=Duke University Press|isbn=9780822330592|location=|pages=112\u201313|language=en}}</ref>\n\n{{flagicon image|Pine Ridge Flag.svg}} [[Republic of Lakotah proposal|Lakotah]]\n* Proposed state: {{flagicon image|Pine Ridge Flag.svg}} [[Republic of Lakotah proposal|Republic of Lakotah]]\n** Ethnic group: [[Lakota people]]\n\n[[File:Flag of Texas.svg|22px|border]] [[Texas]]\n{{Main article|Texas secession movements}}\n* Proposed state: [[File:Flag of Texas.svg|22px|border]] [[Republic of Texas]]\n** Pressure groups: [[Texas Nationalist Movement]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thetnm.org/}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Flag of Vermont.svg|22px|border]] [[Vermont]]\n* Proposed state: Restoration of the [[File:Flag_of_the_Vermont_Republic.svg|22px|border]] [[Vermont Republic]]\n** Political party: Vermont Independence Party<ref>[http://www.wcax.com/story/19502928/vt-independence-party-to-meet-in-montpelier Vt. Independence Party to meet in Montpelier], [[WCAX-TV]] News, September 12, 2012.</ref><ref>[http://www.7dvt.com/vermont-independence-party?filter1&#91;date&#93;=2010-01-15&filter1&#91;time&#93;=00%3A00&filter2&#91;date&#93;=2010-01-15&filter2&#91;time&#93;=23%3A59&timeframe=future Vermont Independence Party convention], Seven Days newspaper, September 2012.</ref>\n** Pressure group: [[File:Flag_of_the_Vermont_Republic.svg|22px|border]] [[Second Vermont Republic]]\n\n\n===Territories===\n{{flag|Puerto Rico}}\n{{main article|Independence movement in Puerto Rico}}\n* Cultural group: [[Puerto Rican people]]\n** Proposed state: {{flag|Puerto Rico|name=Republic of Puerto Rico}}\n*** Political party: [[Puerto Rican Independence Party]] (PIP)\n*** Pressure group: [[Puerto Rican Nationalist Party]], [[Movimiento Independentista Nacional Hostosiano]] (MINH), [[Socialist Front (Puerto Rico)|Socialist Front]] (FS)\n*** Militant organization: [[Boricua Popular Army]] (Macheteros), [[Cadets of the Republic]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Other===\n[[File:Flag of the Confederate States of America (1865).svg|border|22x22px]] [[Confederate States of America]]\n{{main article|Neo-Confederate}}\n* Proposed state: Confederate States of America or [[Southern United States]]\n** Pressure groups: [[League of the South]], [https://freeflorida.org The Florida League of the South], [https://northfloridals.org The North Florida Chapter League of the South], New Confederate Army\n** Militant organization: New Confederate Army<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://thenewconfederatearmy.tripod.com/home.html|title=Home|website=thenewconfederatearmy.tripod.com|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref>\n\n==French Overseas Departments and Collectivities==\n{{Main|Secession in France}}\n\n{{flagicon|France}} [[Martinique]]\n* Proposed state: [[Image:Flag of the Front National de Lib\u00e9ration de la Martinique.svg|22px|border]] Republic of Martinique\n** Political party: [[Martinican Progressive Party]], [[Image:Bandera del MIM.svg|22px|border]] [[Martinican Independence Movement]]\n\n{{flagicon|France}} [[Guadeloupe]] \n* Proposed state: [[Image:FLNG.svg|22px|border]] Republic of Guadeloupe\n** Political party: [[United Guadeloupe, Solidary and Responsible]], [[Progressive Democratic Party of Guadeloupe]], [[Plural Left (Guadeloupe)|Plural Left]] and the [[Guadeloupean Objective]]\n\n{{flagicon|France}} [[Collectivity of Saint Martin|Saint Martin]]\n* Proposed state: [[File:Flag of Saint-Martin (fictional).svg|22px|border]] Republic of Saint Martin\n** Political party: [[Rally Responsibility Success]], [[Succeed Saint Martin]], [[Union for Progress (Saint Martin)|Union for Progress]], [[Union for Progress (Saint Martin)|Union for Progress]] and the [[Democratic Alliance for Saint Martin]]\n\n{{Flagicon|France}} [[Saint Barthelemy]]\n* Proposed state: Republic of Saint Barthelemy\n** Political party: [[Saint Barth First!]]\n\n{{Flagicon|France}} [[Saint Pierre and Miquelon]]\n* Proposed State: Republic of Saint Pierre and Miquelon\n** Political party: [[Together for the Future]], [[Saint Pierre and Miquelon 2000]]\n\n==See also==\n* [[Lists of active separatist movements]]\n* [[List of historical separatist movements]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n{{Separatist movements per continent}}\n{{Secession in Countries}}\n{{Irredentism}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Active Separatist Movements In North America, List Of}}\n[[Ca